master.notes: Duke Ellington And His Orchestra did a series of five recording sessions in New York for Musicraft late in 1946. These tracks were all released as 78rpm singles on the Musicraft label and later compiled in more or less complete form on various labels, under various titles and with variable track listings. The true order of the sessions is:-October 23: Diminuendo In Blue & Magenta Haze-November 25: Sultry Sunset, Happy Go Lucky Local - Part 1, Happy Go Lucky Local - Part 1, Blue Skies-December 5: The Beautiful Indians - Hiawatha, The Beautiful Indians - Minnehaha, Flippant Flurry, Golden Feather- December 11: Overture To Jam Session - Part 1, Overture To Jam Session - Part 2, Jam-A-Ditty-December 18: Tulip Or Turnip & It Shouldn't Happen In A DreamThe last two tracks are only included on the "Complete Musicraft Recordings" CD on Definitive Records.
